.TH HXED 1 "March 2026" "hxed 1.4.X" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
hxed \- modern hex viewer for binary data

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hxed
.RI [ options ] " [" filename ]
.br
cat file.bin |
.B hxed
.RI [ options ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hxed
is a modern hex viewer for inspecting binary data from files or standard input.

It supports multiple output formats, optional ASCII display, colorized output,
searching, range-restricted reading, and raw output for scripting and piping.

If both a filename and data from standard input are provided,
the filename takes precedence.

.SH OPTIONS

.SS Input
.TP
.BR \-f , " \-\-file " " <filename>"
Read input from
.IR filename .
Optional if data is provided via standard input.

.SS Display
.TP
.BR \-m , " \-\-mode " " <num|'name'>"
Output mode:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
0 or
.B hex
.IP \(bu 2
1 or
.B bin
.IP \(bu 2
2 or
.B oct
.IP \(bu 2
3 or
.B dec
.RE
Default is
.B hex .

.TP
.BR \-hm , " \-\-heatmap " " <adaptiv|fixed|none>"
Enable heatmap coloring using 16 colors.
Disabled automatically if color output is disabled.

.TP
.BR \-w , " \-\-width " " <num>"
Number of bytes per line (default: 16).
A value of
.B 0
disables line breaks, but is only valid together with
.BR --raw .

.TP
.BR \-g , " \-\-grouping " " <num>"
Group bytes visually (default: 1).
A value of
.B 0
removes spacing.

.TP
.BR \-a , " \-\-ascii"
Toggle ASCII representation column.

.TP
.BR \-c , " \-\-color"
Toggle colored output.
Disabling color also disables heatmap and string highlighting.

.TP
.BR \-s , " \-\-string"
Toggle string highlighting.

.TP
.BR \-e , " \-\-entropy"
Toggle entropy graph per line.

.TP
.BR \-th , " \-\-toggle-header"
Toggle display of header, footer, and magic byte detection.

.TP
.BR \-sz , " \-\-skip-zero"
Toggle skipping lines containing only zero bytes.

.SS Read Range
.TP
.BR \-o , " \-\-offset " " <num>"
Start reading at byte offset.

.TP
.BR \-l , " \-\-limit " " <num>"
Stop reading at the specified byte position.

.TP
.BR \-r , " \-\-read-size " " <num>"
Read at most the specified number of bytes.

.PP
The options
.B --limit
and
.B --read-size
are mutually exclusive.

.SS Size Suffixes
Numeric values for offset, limit, and read-size support suffixes:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.B k
= 1000
.IP \(bu 2
.B M
= 1000000
.IP \(bu 2
.B G
= 1000000000
.RE

Example:
.B 10k
= 10000 bytes.

.SS Search
.TP
.BR \-se , " \-\-search " " <pattern>"
Search for byte patterns and print matching lines only.

Supported formats:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.B a:<text>
.IP \(bu 2
.B d:<num[,..]>
(decimal bytes)
.IP \(bu 2
.B b:<bits[,..]>
(binary bytes)
.IP \(bu 2
.B x:<hex>
(hex string or comma-separated values)
.RE

.SS Output
.TP
.BR \-p , " \-\-pager"
Toggle pager output.

.TP
.BR \-ro , " \-\-raw"
Enable raw output mode.

In raw mode:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
No colors are used
.IP \(bu 2
No header or footer is displayed
.IP \(bu 2
No addresses are printed
.IP \(bu 2
Only formatted values according to the selected mode are output
.RE

When combined with
.B --width 0 ,
all output is printed on a single line.

.SS Information
.TP
.BR \-h , " \-\-help"
Show help and exit.

.TP
.BR \-v , " \-\-version"
Show version and exit.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B hxed image.png
View a file normally.

.TP
.B hxed -w 32 secret.bin
Show 32 bytes per line.

.TP
.B hxed -c file | less -R
Disable colors and pipe to pager.

.TP
.B echo 'Hello' | hxed
Read from standard input.

.TP
.B hxed -ro -w 0 file > out.txt
Write raw output without line breaks.

.TP
.B hxed -se a:Hello file.bin
Search ASCII text.

.TP
.B hxed -se x:48656c6c6f file.bin
Search hex pattern.

.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
Offsets and sizes must be positive integers.
.IP \(bu 2
Filename takes precedence over standard input.
.IP \(bu 2
Invalid combinations of options will abort execution.
.IP \(bu 2
Toggle flags invert the default state.
.IP \(bu 2
Magic byte detection is disabled when using an offset.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Error.

